OL,4,Cacross the UK: What are your rights?
OL,6,FWhere they can, they should explain
OL,7,Fhow long they expect to be away,
OL,8,Falthough this may be difficult during
OL,9,Ffast-changing situations.
OL,11,FEmployers cannot refuse dependant
OL,12,Fleave if the employee has no other
OL,13,Freasonable option.
OL,15,FHowever, the law only allows for a
OL,16,F"reasonable" amount of time off, and
OL,17,Fthis is not clearly defined.
