OL,4,Cacross the UK: What are your rights?
OL,6,F"It depends on how cooperative the
OL,7,Femployer is going to be in terms of
OL,8,Fhow quickly they will respond to the
OL,9,Frequest," Ms Kennedy said.
OL,11,F"Again, that depends on the work that
OL,12,Fyou're doing and how possible that is,
OL,13,Fbecause obviously, only real office
OL,14,Fworkers can do that."
OL,16,FThere is no automatic right to paid
OL,17,Ftime off for long-term school
OL,18,Fclosures, and many families may
OL,19,Fstruggle if alternative childcare,
OL,20,Fsuch as support from grandparents, is
OL,21,Fnot available.
