OL,4,Cacross the UK: What are your rights?
OL,6,FSome employers may allow you to work
OL,7,Ffrom home, but they are not legally
OL,8,Frequired to agree to this or to pay
OL,9,Fyou if you cannot attend in person.
OL,11,FMs Kennedy said workers cannot be
OL,12,Fpenalised for being unable to travel
OL,13,Fsafely, such as when roads are
OL,14,Fdangerous or public transport is
OL,15,Fsuspended.
OL,17,FHowever, there is no guaranteed right
OL,18,Fto pay in these circumstances and in
OL,19,Fmany cases, employees may be asked to
OL,20,Ftake unpaid leave or use annual leave
OL,21,Finstead.
